Vegetable rice is perfect for a weekend with friends and family. Smoky sausage and rice is a vibrant, flavorful, and downright delicious meal. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 In a small saucepan, boil rice and set aside. Step 2 Place a large sufuria over medium-high.  Add the oil then fry the sausages. Cook until browned on both sides, about 5 minutes. Remove from the pan and set aside. Step 3 On the same sufuria, add the peppers and onion, and sauté for 4-5 minutes. Then add the garlic, salt, and pepper. Cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Remove from the pan and set aside with the sausage. Step 4 Add the tomato paste and about ¾ cup of chicken broth or water, and whisk to combine. Allow the mixture to simmer for 1 minute, then add the paprika and cayenne. Step 5 Stir in the cooked rice, sausage, pepper, and onions until combined. Garnish with chopped parsley, serve immediately with a cold beverage.